# No Unsolicited Documentation

## Rule
Do not create markdown files or documentation unless explicitly requested by the user.

## Files to NEVER Create Without User Request
- PROJECT_SUMMARY.md
- SUMMARY.md
- RECAP.md
- CHANGELOG.md
- FEATURES.md
- INSTALL.md
- QUICKSTART.md
- GETTING_STARTED.md
- Any .md file in docs/ folder
- Any documentation file
- Any guide or tutorial file
- Any "how-to" file

## When This Rule Applies
- After completing tasks
- After making changes
- During project setup
- When adding new features
- At any point during development
- When integrating new libraries

## Only Exception
- README.md - ONLY if it's a new project with no README
- If user explicitly says "create a guide" or "write documentation"

## Why This Rule Exists
The user will create their own documentation when they want it. Unsolicited markdown files clutter the project and are rarely what the user actually needs.
